    "actor_description": "It catches. My attention cinches down until everything else turns to background noise. I can feel myself holding still on purpose—breath quieter, eyes wanting to miss nothing. Little details start to matter: tiny shifts, patterns, the next piece that will make it click. Interruptions don’t just annoy me—they bounce off, like they can’t get traction.",
    "description_text": "{actor} seems to narrow to a single point—gaze fixed, blink rate dropping, body stilled as if movement would ruin the signal. Their responses, if any, come a beat late and more precise than usual, like their attention is fully spoken for.",
